==Building canals==
# Open the ''Waterways construction'' toolbar by clicking the [[File:en/Manual html m2cc0c4cd.png]] button.<br/>[[File:en/Dock toolbar.png|frame|none|The Waterways construction toolbar.]]
# Click on the ''Build canal'' button [[File:en/Build canal.png]]. Remember, you can right click on any button if you ever want a description of what it does.
# Place the cursor on any flat tile of land and then left-click to place the canal tile. You can also click and drag to place longer stretches of canal.<br/>[[File:en/Building-canals-1.png|frame|none|Building a canal.]]

Once the canal is built, it's time to connect it to a lower level of water using locks.

If you need to build a dock - for example once the canal is close enough to the industry you're targeting - then just build a large (and expensive!) area for the ships to manoeuver and to build the dock, like in the next picture:

